```

- VSCode Version: 1.7.1
- OS Version: Mac OSX 10.12

I have a Typescript/React/TSX project. Since my team changed from grunt to webpack and  I updated VSCode, I can't get my global imports work as before, as well as the JSX recognition:

> [ts] Cannot find module 'react'.
> [ts] Cannot find module 'd3-scale'.
> [ts] Cannot use JSX unless the '--jsx' flag is provided.

We have a typings file, so I tried to fix this by making a include rule inside the tsconfig file:

```JSON
{
    "compilerOptions": {
        "target": "es6",
        "jsx": "react",
        "sourceMap": true
    },
    "include": [
        "./src/**/*",
        "./typings/index.d.ts"
    ],
    "exclude": [
        "node_modules"
    ]
}
```

But this file, which is at the root of the project, seems just ignored by VSCode, as doing a manual include does the job, nor the tsconfig.json file:

```TypeScript
/// <reference path="../typings/index.d.ts" />

// Global imports
import * as React from 'react';
import * as d3Scale from 'd3-scale';
// Ok!
```

I don't feel like I'm doing something wrong, but  tout hasard, this are my workspace settings:

```JSON
{
    "typescript.tsdk": "./node_modules/typescript/lib"
}
```

Best regards
